intro: Galatella × feketegaborii, commonly known as the Black Gabor's galatella, is a hybrid plant in the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its tall, slender stems and finely divided, fern-like leaves. The plant produces small, white to pale yellow flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the carrot family. It thrives in moist, well-drained soils and is often found in woodland or streamside habitats. Due to its ornamental value, it is occasionally cultivated in gardens.
